sections.content:
The BFM consists of generating all the TPOs of the objects and then selecting all of them that are compatible with each PPO (called CTPOs) and calculating their corresponding Frobenius distances. As the final result for the normalized distance, we take either:
• Optim: normalized distance based on the optimistic decision-making attitude (i.e., the minimum of Frobenius distance among all possible normalized distances of CTPOs);
• Pessim: normalized distance based on the pessimistic decision-making attitude (i.e., the maximum Frobenius distance among all possible normalized distances of CTPOs);
• Aver: normalized distance based on the averaged decision-making attitude of all possible normalized distances of CTPOs;
• Hurwicz: normalized distance based on Hurwicz attitude [14], [15] which is a weighted balance between the min and max decision-making attitudes.
